 We\nalso found that the UV light curve mostly traced the X-ray curve, but a short\ndipping event was observed in both the UV and the X-ray bands with a 3.5-day\nX-ray time lag. This can be interpreted as the radial inflow of accreting\nmatter from the outer UV region to the inner X-ray region.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Jun 2014 08:05:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 8 Jul 2014 18:10:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-07-09"}
